# Suka Smart Assistant — Batch Cooking Scratch Plan
# Style: BLUF + actionable checklists + event hooks
# Use: keep this file open while you implement; check items off; commit early/often

0) BLUF
- We are building an intuitive Batch Cooking flow that:
  • Lets users drag recipes from the Recipe Vault into a Batch Session.
  • Merges steps into an integrated timeline with parallel-safe tasks and MultiTimerPanel.
  • Honors household taste prefs (doneness, softness/tenderness, spice tolerance, fat preference).
  • Syncs ingredients ⇄ Inventory, auto-generates Prep Checklists & Labels, and logs preservation (pressure canning, freezing, dehydrating, curing, beer/wine).
  • Emits events for the automation runtime so other modules react (calendar, inventory, garden, storehouse).

1) One-liners (Job → Output → Next Best Action → Events)
• Batch Cooking: “Build a session → integrated timeline + timers + labels → ‘Start Session’ → batch.started”
• Prep: “Consolidate ingredients → prep checklist + station map → ‘Send to Print’ → prep.checklist.created”
• Cook: “Run timers → live step tracker + voice prompts → ‘Mark steps done’ → batch.step.completed”
• Labeling: “Autofill labels (name/date/preservation) → printable PDF → ‘Print labels’ → labels.printed”
• Inventory Sync: “Delta items used → inventory update patch → ‘Apply’ → inventory.updated”
• Preservation: “Select preservation per dish → tracker entries → ‘Log preservation’ → preservation.logged”
• Garden Tie-ins: “Harvest pulled for recipes → decrement harvest bins → ‘Move to root cellar’ → harvest.logged”
• Calendar: “Session blocks + cooling/cure times → calendar events → ‘Share schedule’ → calendar.synced”
• Recovery: “If session stalls → suggest swap/shortcuts → ‘Apply recovery’ → batch.recovery.applied”

