5) UI Acceptance Criteria (quick)
☐ Horizontal, raised cards layout for Session Planner & MultiTimerPanel.
☐ Drag from Recipe Vault → Batch Session queue works (multi-select + drag).
☐ Taste toggles (doneness/softness/spice/fat) visibly affect steps & timers.
☐ One-click: “Generate Prep Checklist”, “Generate Labels”, “Start Session”.
☐ Live step tracker + voice + toasts; timers persist on route change.
☐ Inventory delta preview with “Apply” (safe patch + undo).
☐ Preservation trackers write entries + produce labels where relevant.
☐ Calendar sync creates events for session window + critical timings.

6) Domain Preferences to honor (HouseholdProfile / MealPrefs)
- Doneness: rare/med-rare/medium/med-well/well for meats
- Softness/Tenderness: softer | normal | firmer
- Spice Tolerance: mild | medium | hot
- Fat Preference: leaner | balanced | rich
- Texture Goals: crispy | tender | chewy | flaky (per dish)
- Kosher/Torah constraints: no pork/shellfish; separation logic when needed
- Appliances: pressure cooker, dehydrator, smoker, water bath, pressure canner
- Batch Goal: target servings, storage method split (e.g., 50% freeze, 30% can, 20% fresh)

7) Event Contract (emit/subscribe)
- Emit:
  • batch.started, batch.paused, batch.resumed, batch.completed
  • batch.step.completed (payload: {stepId, recipeId, ts})
  • prep.checklist.created (payload: {pdfUrl, items})
  • labels.printed (payload: {pdfUrl, count})
  • inventory.updated (payload: {delta, patchId})
  • preservation.logged (payload: {method, items, ts})
  • calendar.synced (payload: {events})
  • batch.recovery.applied (payload: {suggestions})
- Subscribe:
  • recipes.consolidated → prefill selectable recipes
  • garden.harvest.available → suggest substitutions
  • inventory.low → warn & auto-adjust shopping checklist
  • user.prefs.updated → recompute timeline/temps

8) Minimal Data Shapes (copy into agents as JSDoc or typedefs)
/**
 * @typedef {Object} BatchSession
 * @prop {string} id
 * @prop {string} name
 * @prop {Date} createdAt
 * @prop {string[]} recipeIds
 * @prop {SessionPrefs} prefs
 * @prop {IntegratedStep[]} timeline
 * @prop {InventoryDelta} inventoryDelta
 */

/** SessionPrefs includes doneness/softness/spice/fat */
{
  "doneness": {"beef":"medium","lamb":"medium","chicken":"well"},
  "softness": "tender",
  "spice": "medium",
  "fat": "balanced",
  "textureGoals": {"fried-chicken":"crispy","stew":"tender"},
  "appliances": ["pressure_cooker","pressure_canner","dehydrator","smoker"],
  "targets": {"servingsTotal": 32, "preservationSplit": {"freeze":0.5,"can":0.3,"fresh":0.2}}
}

/** IntegratedStep (flattened, parallel-safe) */
{
  "id":"step-uuid",
  "recipeId":"r1",
  "startsAfter":"preheat-oven",
  "durationSec": 420,
  "blocking": false,
  "appliance":"oven",
  "action":"Bake thighs @400°F until 165°F (approx 18 min). Crisp goal.",
  "thermoTargetF": 165,
  "donenessTuning": {"beef":"medium","lamb":"medium"},
  "softnessTuning": "tender",
  "spiceTuning": "medium",
  "labels": ["hot-surface","timer","crispy-target"]
}

/** InventoryDelta */
{
  "consume":[ {"sku":"CHICKEN_THIGH","qty":12,"unit":"pcs"}, {"sku":"OIL_AVO","qty":180,"unit":"ml"} ],
  "produce":[ {"sku":"FRIED_CHICKEN_MEAL","qty":12,"unit":"serving","preservation":"freeze"} ],
  "missing":[ {"sku":"PAPRIKA_SMOKED","qty":10,"unit":"g"} ]
}

9) Pseudocode — Agent timeline (src/agents/batchCookingShim.js)
/*
export async function buildIntegratedTimeline(selectedRecipes, prefs, equipment){
  const steps = flattenRecipeSteps(selectedRecipes);
  const tuned = applyTasteTuning(steps, prefs); // doneness/softness/spice/fat/texture
  const sequenced = topologicalSchedule(tuned); // resolve deps
  const parallelized = packParallel(sequenced, equipment); // avoid appliance conflicts
  const withThermo = injectThermoTargets(parallelized, prefs);
  return withThermo;
}
*/

10) UI Wiring Notes
- Taste toggles should immediately regenerate the timeline and timers.
- “Generate Prep Checklist” pulls from tuned steps: ingredients→actions→tools.
- “Label Printer” consumes produce[] from InventoryDelta plus preservation method & reheat.
- MultiTimerPanel registers 1 timer per IntegratedStep that has durationSec (no subplots).
- Voice/Toasts: “Preheat complete”, “Start sear”, “Flip now”, “Pull at 135°F”, “Rest 10 min”…

